  "texts": [
    "The Partitioning Around Medoids (PAM) algorithm 63 was applied to identify clusters because it has the robustness to outliers 64 and performs better than the popular k-means algorithm 65.",
    "Euclidean distance and the Silhouette method were employed for cluster evaluation.",
    "The Silhouette width assesses the cohesion of members in clusters, serving as a widely used validation metric that aggregates the similarity of an observations to their own cluster relative to their nearest neighboring cluster.",
    "With a range from -1 to 1, higher values signify better clustering.",
    "The average Silhouette width was calculated for varying cluster numbers, ranging from 2 to 10, using the PAM algorithm."
  ],
